> <i>Or assuming hello is a global in your dart example</i><p>The way it&#x27;s written implies that it&#x27;s somewhere inside some block, because &quot;main()&quot; is always the entry point. I wrote it like that because I couldn&#x27;t be bothered to figure out how this stuff works in Scheme.<p>With entry point:<p><pre><code>  main() => print(&#x27;Hello World&#x27;);
</code></pre>
Alternatively:<p><pre><code>  main() {
    print(&#x27;Hello World&#x27;);
  }</code></pre>
